Thank you to the Old Tappan Environmental Commission (OTEC) for hosting a photo contest, which was open to our middle school students. The participating-students found and documented beauty in our local environment! Congratulations to all involved!

The following photos were selected as winning submissions:

First Place - Sky with Trees (Grade 8 Student)
Second Place - Butterfly on Flowers (Grade 6 Student)
Third Place - Lizard on a Rock (Grade 7 Student)
Fourth Place - Bird on the Birdhouse (Grade 6 Student)
Fourth Place - Starter Plants (Grade 5 Student)

post_text: Today, members of NVOT's Future Business Leaders of America (FBLA) have been facilitating a day's worth of lessons at every grade-level. The state requires that middle school students receive financial literacy instruction. Classes are engaging in fun, authentic activities that cover career pathways, budgeting, responsible spending & saving, credit & debt, and other valuable information and life skills. Today's experience is a unique addition to the financial literacy lessons infused into the curriculum by CDW teachers throughout the year. 💳💲👍💸

post_text:
I hope everyone’s weekend is off to a great start. Thank you to those who came out to Thursday night’s Adventure Venture! I was blown away by the entire event, and it was easy to see how much time, energy, and love was put into the work by our students and also Ms. Gambuti. The Art Show was also equally amazing, and we think separating these two events (1) gives student work more time/space to shine, and (2) serves as an excuse to have yet another “family night” at TBD…Finally, this week’s Kindergarten Screening was a blast. It was fun to see to see all of the new, smiling faces at TBD!

See below for this week's newsletter.

post_text:
I hope everyone is enjoying the week, and hopefully this rain will go away. Last night I was able to catch Avengers: Endgame, which I can recommend (although I didn’t love it as much as some of the reviews out there).

I look forward to seeing everyone at the Art Show on Tuesday night. Ms. Clark and the PTO have been working hard to reimagine this event from the ground up, and we know everyone is going to love it!

See below for this week's newsletter.
